frameDefinitions: A State_of_affairs is evaluated as good (or bad), against a background assumption that previously, the State_of_affairs was thought to be unlikely to occur.

An Agent has attempted to achieve a Goal, and the actual outcome of the Agent's action has been resolved, so that it either specifically matches the Agent's intent (e.g. success) or does not match it (e.g. failure).
The words in this frame involve an Undesirable_event which affects the Patient negatively.
A Competition comes to an end, with a Competitor tying, winning, or losing against an Opponent (or opponents) according to their Score.
A Person or Institution is being described in terms of their wealthiness, in other words the amount of money in their possession.
frameExamples: He <t>pulled</t> <t>off</t> his April Fool's Day prank by the barest of margins .
The first <t>calamity</t> was a disastrous trade war with Holland.
Unbelievable--he <t>lost</t> the gold medal by just .02 points!

The <fen>Role</fen> filled by the <fen>Protagonist</fen>.

The location where the <fen>Protagonist</fen> has luck.

This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the attempt succeeds or fails.
The place where an attempt succeeds or fails.
The undesirable event which occurs.

When the <fen>Undesirable_Event</fen> occurs.
Where the <fen>Undesirable_Event</fen> takes place.
The individual involved in the <fen>Competition</fen>.
The individual that the <fen>Competitor</fen> has been competing against.
The individuals who compete against each other.
The event in which the <fen>Competitors</fen> compete with each other.
The time at which the <fen>Competition</fen> takes place.
The location at which the <fen>Competition</fen> takes place.
The individual or individuals whose wealthiness is being described.
A group which has (or lacks) possession of some resource.

<fex>On the bridge</fex> he succeeded in putting the wig on the corpse.
